item.description: Sample Information SHA25 SHA1 MD5 058c764614c8b0b457852a71ab93b559f81abb9e13b7fc2d6c6a4962881bf062 550faad818bb76d01333f0469ea6e715feaef2f0 a4e4a7b64b91de9bf076b0581e0604b9 First Stage The script starts by defining the ".proc()" function and adding it as a method to the String[] type. The function, once called will convert content to string and then perform eval(). This is used within the code to launch code saved as string. ![[Pasted image 20230731230644.png]] The second function defined in the same way is ".nan()". This code simply inverts the contents of an array of length 3.
